727
01:09:41,901 --> 01:09:43,971
- Who is that asshole?
- Lillo De Gregorio.

728
01:09:44,101 --> 01:09:47,252
The greatest modern art collector
in this debauched country.

729
01:09:47,541 --> 01:09:51,819
- What's Jep's floozy friend wearing?
- l don't know.

730
01:09:51,981 --> 01:09:55,132
Jep's proving to be
a disappointment.

731
01:09:55,301 --> 01:09:58,338
- Good evening, countess.
- Hello, you're looking well.

732
01:09:58,541 --> 01:10:02,739
l wish l could say that same
about the count. Hello, ladies!

733
01:10:03,141 --> 01:10:06,019
Are you stupid?
You're distracting my artist.

734
01:10:06,141 --> 01:10:07,540
Dad, we're having fun.

735
01:10:07,741 --> 01:10:10,175
Carmelina, come and do some work.

736
01:10:10,301 --> 01:10:12,098
Mom, l want to play here.

737
01:10:12,221 --> 01:10:15,293
- Has this human being gone mad?
- We'll sort it out.

738
01:10:15,461 --> 01:10:18,658
- l'm not coming, l'm staying here.
- You don't mean that.

739
01:10:18,781 --> 01:10:20,976
Europe's greatest gallery owners
are outside.

740
01:10:21,101 --> 01:10:24,889
lf you show them what you can do
then ours will be a happy family.

741
01:10:25,021 --> 01:10:27,774
But l'm already happy,
l want to be a vet one day.

742
01:10:27,941 --> 01:10:32,810
Get to bed, you two!
My kids are going to bed.

743
01:10:32,981 --> 01:10:33,891
Come.

744
01:10:34,021 --> 01:10:36,455
l'll go to bed too.
l'm a kid too.

745
01:10:41,461 --> 01:10:43,736
She blushes and says:

746
01:10:43,941 --> 01:10:48,093
"Forgive me, l didn't know
you loved me so much.

747
01:10:48,501 --> 01:10:51,459
My ignorance is obscene."

748
01:10:51,941 --> 01:10:54,171
He looks at her, reassuringly,
and says:

749
01:10:54,381 --> 01:10:57,578
"Let me defend our love".

750
01:10:57,741 --> 01:11:00,460
How's that for the start
of the second act?

751
01:11:00,581 --> 01:11:02,572
You've written a pile of shit.

752
01:13:53,221 --> 01:13:55,132
That girl was crying.

753
01:13:55,221 --> 01:13:57,894
Nonsense!
That girl earns millions!

754
01:13:59,021 --> 01:14:00,852
Excuse me a moment.

755
01:14:03,781 --> 01:14:06,659
- Hi, Stefano.
- Hi.

756
01:14:07,301 --> 01:14:10,976
- The catering's gone downhill.
- Rome's gone downhill.

757
01:14:11,061 --> 01:14:12,460
Steeply downhill!

758
01:14:15,941 --> 01:14:18,091
Do you have the case with you?

759
01:14:20,821 --> 01:14:23,335
- l always do.
- You up for it?

760
01:15:27,621 --> 01:15:28,656
See that?

761
01:15:33,781 --> 01:15:38,013
Stefano has the keys to Rome's
most beautiful buildings.

762
01:15:39,621 --> 01:15:41,134
ls he a doorman?

763
01:15:42,901 --> 01:15:45,176
No, he's not a doorman.

764
01:15:45,501 --> 01:15:47,935
He's friends with princesses.

765
01:15:50,981 --> 01:15:52,334
Are you ready?

766
01:15:53,301 --> 01:15:54,700
Come with me.

767
01:17:54,541 --> 01:17:56,736
Good evening, Princesses.

768
01:17:56,861 --> 01:17:59,011
Good evening.

769
01:18:11,741 --> 01:18:13,493
How come you have all these keys?

770
01:18:15,421 --> 01:18:17,059
Because...

771
01:18:18,581 --> 01:18:20,412
l'm a trustworthy person.

772
01:18:35,381 --> 01:18:39,579
Did you see? lt looked huge,
but it's tiny.

773
01:18:41,261 --> 01:18:44,458
Stay still, l'll take a photo of you.
Don't move.

774
01:18:48,021 --> 01:18:50,296
That's no good.
Laugh.

775
01:18:52,621 --> 01:18:54,100
Got it?

776
01:18:54,501 --> 01:18:56,651
Yes, that's good.

777
01:19:47,981 --> 01:19:50,939
Many think that a funeral,

778
01:19:51,061 --> 01:19:54,212
is a fortuitous event,
without any rules.

779
01:19:54,901 --> 01:19:56,380
That's not true.

780
01:19:56,901 --> 01:20:00,576
A funeral is a high-society event
par excellence.

781
01:20:02,061 --> 01:20:05,337
You must never forget
that at a funeral

782
01:20:06,181 --> 01:20:08,297
you are appearing on stage.

783
01:20:12,541 --> 01:20:14,020
Nice.

784
01:20:14,941 --> 01:20:16,579
Nice, but try the other one.

785
01:20:18,461 --> 01:20:23,330
You must patiently wait
for the relatives to disperse.

786
01:20:23,821 --> 01:20:28,690
Once you are sure
that all the guests are seated...

787
01:20:28,901 --> 01:20:32,530
only at that point, may you offer
your condolences to the family.

788
01:20:33,061 --> 01:20:36,974
ln this way, everyone will see you.

789
01:20:37,221 --> 01:20:39,610
You take the mourner's hands,

790
01:20:39,781 --> 01:20:43,410
and rest yours on their arms.

791
01:20:43,821 --> 01:20:47,450
You whisper something to them,
a comforting phrase,

792
01:20:47,661 --> 01:20:49,652
said with authority.

793
01:20:49,781 --> 01:20:52,136
For example:

794
01:20:52,261 --> 01:20:56,857
"ln the days to come,
when you feel the void,

795
01:20:57,541 --> 01:21:01,978
l want you to know
that you can always count on me."

796
01:21:03,461 --> 01:21:05,338
The public will ask...

797
01:21:06,981 --> 01:21:09,859
"What's Jep Gambardella saying?"

798
01:21:22,541 --> 01:21:24,532
This is definitely the right dress.

799
01:21:29,621 --> 01:21:34,058
You're allowed to retire
to a corner by yourself,

800
01:21:34,541 --> 01:21:37,738
as if contemplating your sorrow.

801
01:21:39,141 --> 01:21:43,612
However, another matter
must be approached with shrewdness.

802
01:21:44,301 --> 01:21:48,692
The chosen place needs
to be isolated

803
01:21:48,821 --> 01:21:50,857
but clearly visible
to the public.

804
01:21:51,581 --> 01:21:57,690
Besides, a performance is good when
it is devoid of any superfluity.

805
01:22:00,061 --> 01:22:01,813
So, the fundamental rule:

806
01:22:03,421 --> 01:22:05,810
one must never cry at a funeral.

807
01:22:06,941 --> 01:22:09,933
You must never steal the show
from the family's sorrow.

808
01:22:10,061 --> 01:22:13,133
That is forbidden.

809
01:22:16,061 --> 01:22:17,813
Because it is immoral.

810
01:22:54,421 --> 01:22:56,093
Viola.

811
01:23:04,421 --> 01:23:08,937
ln the days to come,
when you feel the void,

812
01:23:10,181 --> 01:23:12,456
you can always count on me.

813
01:24:00,581 --> 01:24:06,099
Now l ask Andrea's friends
to come forward,

814
01:24:07,981 --> 01:24:10,814
so that the coffin
may be carried outside.

815
01:24:32,341 --> 01:24:33,410
Your back!

816
01:25:42,301 --> 01:25:44,576
lt was nice not making love.

817
01:25:46,341 --> 01:25:48,218
lt was nice loving each other.

818
01:25:49,021 --> 01:25:52,650
l'd forgotten what loving someone
was about, l'd forgotten that.

819
01:25:59,381 --> 01:26:01,941
l spend all my money to cure myself.

820
01:26:10,701 --> 01:26:12,692
Your breakfast.

821
01:26:13,781 --> 01:26:16,818
Come on, l'm taking you to see
a sea monster today.

822
01:26:37,661 --> 01:26:39,174
Your breakfast.

823
01:26:41,341 --> 01:26:43,332
Five more minutes.

824
01:26:50,181 --> 01:26:52,217
Can you see the sea?

825
01:26:58,981 --> 01:27:00,699
Where?

826
01:27:00,861 --> 01:27:02,533
On the ceiling.

827
01:27:08,621 --> 01:27:10,657
Yes, l can see it.

828
01:28:41,301 --> 01:28:44,054
Who's going to look after you now?

829
01:28:58,421 --> 01:29:02,334
l'm sorry about your daughter.
My condolences.

830
01:29:27,701 --> 01:29:33,458
l spent all my summers
making plans for September.

831
01:29:33,581 --> 01:29:35,173
Not any longer.

832
01:29:36,621 --> 01:29:40,739
Now l spend the summer
remembering the good intentions

833
01:29:41,261 --> 01:29:43,172
which vanished.

834
01:29:43,741 --> 01:29:47,620
ln part because of laziness,
in part because of carelessness.

835
01:29:50,821 --> 01:29:53,654
What's wrong
with feeling nostalgic?

836
01:29:55,181 --> 01:29:57,251
lt's the only distraction left
for those

837
01:29:57,381 --> 01:29:59,895
who've no faith
in the future!

838
01:30:03,541 --> 01:30:05,338
Without rain...

839
01:30:05,781 --> 01:30:10,172
August is coming to an end
and September isn't arriving.

840
01:30:11,541 --> 01:30:13,850
And l'm so ordinary!

841
01:30:14,541 --> 01:30:16,850
But there's no need to worry.

842
01:30:17,261 --> 01:30:20,219
lt's all right, it's okay.

843
01:30:27,741 --> 01:30:29,140
Bravo!

844
01:30:44,341 --> 01:30:45,694
Thank you.

845
01:31:31,301 --> 01:31:33,656
What are you doing here?

846
01:31:34,541 --> 01:31:37,931
Arturo!
Why are you here?

847
01:31:38,101 --> 01:31:41,411
Don't you see?
l'm rehearsing my magic show.

848
01:31:41,541 --> 01:31:45,500
This is tomorrow's special number:
the vanishing giraffe.

849
01:31:46,261 --> 01:31:47,979
You can make this giraffe vanish?

850
01:31:48,101 --> 01:31:51,059
Of course l can make
the giraffe vanish!

851
01:31:52,581 --> 01:31:54,970
Then make me vanish too.

852
01:31:56,421 --> 01:32:02,132
Jep, do you think that if l could
really make people vanish

853
01:32:02,541 --> 01:32:06,375
l'd still be here at my age
playing these circus games?

854
01:32:07,621 --> 01:32:09,179
lt's just a trick.

855
01:32:13,501 --> 01:32:15,139
lt's just a trick!

856
01:32:24,541 --> 01:32:26,497
Romano, how did it go?

857
01:32:26,741 --> 01:32:28,652
Well, they clapped.

858
01:32:28,981 --> 01:32:30,733
l'm glad.

859
01:32:31,061 --> 01:32:33,734
- So why are you so sad?
- l'm not sad.

860
01:32:34,021 --> 01:32:35,534
What's with the giraffe?

861
01:32:35,701 --> 01:32:38,454
For a magic show.
l'll come and see you tomorrow.

862
01:32:38,621 --> 01:32:40,452
l'm not doing the show tomorrow.

863
01:32:41,341 --> 01:32:43,013
Why not? You said it went well.

864
01:32:43,141 --> 01:32:47,896
l'm leaving, l'm going back
to my home town, for good.

865
01:32:48,141 --> 01:32:51,611
l won't even pack up my things,
l'll leave it all.

866
01:32:53,981 --> 01:32:57,257
l've lived in this city
for 40 years.

867
01:32:58,061 --> 01:33:00,256
And in the end l thought...

868
01:33:01,781 --> 01:33:04,454
the only person
who deserved a goodbye

869
01:33:04,861 --> 01:33:06,692
was you.

870
01:33:08,701 --> 01:33:10,771
So you're leaving?

871
01:33:13,021 --> 01:33:15,933
Romano... why are you leaving?

872
01:33:16,421 --> 01:33:18,855
Rome has really disappointed me.

873
01:33:24,461 --> 01:33:26,099
Bye, Jep.

874
01:33:45,341 --> 01:33:46,899
See?

875
01:34:15,301 --> 01:34:18,338
- Want some coffee?
- No, thanks. l know you're busy.

876
01:34:18,501 --> 01:34:20,173
l need to ask you something.

877
01:34:20,701 --> 01:34:22,180
Go ahead.

878
01:34:26,301 --> 01:34:28,576
Why did Elisa leave me?

879
01:34:31,661 --> 01:34:33,333
l don't know.

880
01:34:33,461 --> 01:34:37,340
Didn't she say anything about it
in her diary?

881
01:34:37,941 --> 01:34:40,011
No, l don't think so.

882
01:34:43,021 --> 01:34:46,730
Would you be offended
if l asked to read it?

883
01:34:46,901 --> 01:34:49,574
No, l wouldn't.

884
01:34:50,181 --> 01:34:52,456
ln fact, l'd understand.

885
01:34:54,221 --> 01:34:56,496
But l'm afraid l can't
let you read it.

886
01:34:56,661 --> 01:34:57,650
Why not?

887
01:34:58,621 --> 01:35:01,340
Because a few days after the
funeral, l threw it away.

888
01:35:06,941 --> 01:35:09,011
May l introduce you
to my girlfriend?

889
01:35:10,501 --> 01:35:12,810
Hello, my name's Polina.

890
01:35:15,821 --> 01:35:18,460
Like Polina in "The Gambler"
by Dostoyevsky.

891
01:35:24,541 --> 01:35:26,372
What are you doing tonight?

892
01:35:28,101 --> 01:35:29,978
Nothing.

893
01:35:30,541 --> 01:35:32,418
Polina's going to finish ironing...

894
01:35:33,301 --> 01:35:35,531
then we'll drink a glass
of red wine.

895
01:35:36,261 --> 01:35:39,856
We'll watch some television
and go to bed.

896
01:35:41,021 --> 01:35:41,976
What about you?

897
01:35:43,621 --> 01:35:48,092
l'll have a lot of drinks, but not
so many as to become unruly.

898
01:35:48,901 --> 01:35:51,017
And then...

899
01:35:52,021 --> 01:35:56,412
when you'll be getting up
l'll be going to bed.

900
01:36:03,061 --> 01:36:06,212
What lovely people you are!

901
01:36:16,221 --> 01:36:18,291
l love doing the train!

902
01:36:22,661 --> 01:36:24,140
l'll screw you.

903
01:36:26,501 --> 01:36:28,492
"Who am l?"

904
01:36:30,141 --> 01:36:33,178
That's how
one of Breton's novels began.

905
01:36:34,061 --> 01:36:37,133
And of course in the book
there's no reply.

906
01:36:38,141 --> 01:36:40,450
- Did you hear about Viola?
- What?

907
01:36:40,661 --> 01:36:42,174
She's donating everything
to the church.

908
01:36:43,061 --> 01:36:47,532
She works in the parish
and is going to volunteer in Africa.

909
01:36:47,821 --> 01:36:52,497
The trains at our parties
are the best ones in Rome!

910
01:36:53,341 --> 01:36:55,332
- You think so?
- l do.

911
01:36:56,861 --> 01:37:00,376
They're the best because
they go nowhere.

912
01:37:11,141 --> 01:37:13,496
- Well?
- lt's wonderful, thank you.

913
01:37:13,621 --> 01:37:16,181
Come on, it's all gone.

914
01:37:16,301 --> 01:37:19,737
Tell me why you left me, please.

915
01:37:19,861 --> 01:37:22,170
l want an explanation, please!

916
01:37:23,021 --> 01:37:26,058
Go away!
Get out! Get out!

917
01:37:50,901 --> 01:37:52,732
You see all these people?

918
01:37:53,781 --> 01:37:55,772
They can't do anything.

919
01:37:56,341 --> 01:37:58,980
But l know how to do something.

920
01:37:59,741 --> 01:38:02,414
We know how to do something.

921
01:38:03,701 --> 01:38:05,453
How sweet!

922
01:38:47,821 --> 01:38:52,053
They've been asking me for years
why l don't write another novel.

923
01:38:53,221 --> 01:38:55,212
But look at these people.

924
01:38:56,221 --> 01:38:58,337
This wildlife!

925
01:38:59,301 --> 01:39:02,373
This is my life
and it's nothing.

926
01:39:05,661 --> 01:39:08,380
Flaubert wanted to write a book
about nothing but he failed,

927
01:39:08,501 --> 01:39:10,651
so could l do it?

928
01:39:17,341 --> 01:39:19,980
lt's nice.
Thanks, rascal.

929
01:39:33,421 --> 01:39:35,651
What inspired this exhibition?

930
01:39:36,621 --> 01:39:39,738
lt wasn't my idea
to do this photo exhibition.

931
01:39:39,861 --> 01:39:42,011
lt was my father's idea.

932
01:39:42,861 --> 01:39:46,092
When l was born, he starting taking
photos of me, every day.

933
01:39:46,301 --> 01:39:48,178
One photo per day.

934
01:39:48,741 --> 01:39:51,050
He never forgot, not even once.

935
01:39:51,781 --> 01:39:55,456
From the age of 14 upwards,
l continued.

936
01:39:56,141 --> 01:39:59,258
l photographed myself every day.

937
01:40:03,541 --> 01:40:05,133
Go ahead.

938
01:41:44,541 --> 01:41:47,214
- Cardinal!
- Your Eminence!

939
01:41:50,221 --> 01:41:52,689
Cardinal,
when will The Saint arrive in Rome?

940
01:41:52,821 --> 01:41:56,097
On Thursday,
but please don't call her The Saint.

941
01:41:56,221 --> 01:42:00,214
She is a Saint but not technically.

942
01:42:01,141 --> 01:42:03,939
Tell me something,
who is that cardinal?

943
01:42:04,061 --> 01:42:06,370
- That's Bellucci.
- Bellucci?

944
01:42:06,501 --> 01:42:08,253
- The one in line to be...
- Exactly.

945
01:42:08,381 --> 01:42:10,372
The papal throne awaits him.

946
01:42:10,581 --> 01:42:13,175
l met him at Giada Ricci's
carnival party.

947
01:42:13,301 --> 01:42:16,418
Rumour has it that he used to be
Europe's best exorcist.

948
01:42:16,541 --> 01:42:18,259
- Are you pulling my leg?
- No.

949
01:42:19,101 --> 01:42:20,853
l never joke about the devil.

950
01:42:21,381 --> 01:42:24,578
Do you know l'm very, very bored.

951
01:42:25,861 --> 01:42:28,580
We're having a great, great time.

952
01:42:29,261 --> 01:42:30,979
You cut up the duck.

953
01:42:31,101 --> 01:42:36,255
Cook it on a high flame
for 15 minutes.

954
01:42:36,381 --> 01:42:38,053
At that point...

955
01:42:38,221 --> 01:42:41,019
Cardinal, do you remember me?
Lello Cava.

956
01:42:41,141 --> 01:42:45,054
We met at Giada Ricci's party.
l was dressed as an escort.

957
01:42:45,501 --> 01:42:48,015
Come, they're starting
to serve lunch.

958
01:42:48,301 --> 01:42:51,737
l'd like you meet my writer friend,
Jep Gambardella.

959
01:42:52,421 --> 01:42:56,858
A writer!
This country needs writers.

960
01:42:56,981 --> 01:42:59,097
Actually l thought it was more
in need of priests.

961
01:42:59,261 --> 01:43:00,057
Help.

962
01:43:00,181 --> 01:43:03,332
- May l ask you a question?
- Of course, my dear man.

963
01:43:03,461 --> 01:43:06,373
Well, for some time now...

964
01:43:12,061 --> 01:43:14,859
from a spiritual point of view...

965
01:43:15,861 --> 01:43:20,173
- Skunk hunt?
- Of course, l'll lead the way!

966
01:43:20,301 --> 01:43:23,532
l know the Tebaldi grounds well.

967
01:43:29,301 --> 01:43:33,419
Jep Gambardella, the king
of socialites! You're losing it.

968
01:43:33,541 --> 01:43:38,740
l've been losing it for 40 years.
lt's a steady decline.

969
01:43:42,821 --> 01:43:48,373
Tell me something, Stefania.
Have we ever slept with each other?

970
01:43:49,101 --> 01:43:51,410
Of course not!

971
01:43:55,821 --> 01:43:59,973
That's an awfully big mistake!
We must make amends, immediately.

972
01:44:00,941 --> 01:44:02,932
ldiot.

973
01:44:05,501 --> 01:44:07,332
Thank goodness.

974
01:44:08,581 --> 01:44:11,653
We still have something nice
to do together.

975
01:44:14,581 --> 01:44:17,653
The future is marvellous, Stefania.

976
01:44:51,781 --> 01:44:54,693
To be honest, Catellani
hasn't had many brushed fabrics

977
01:44:54,821 --> 01:44:56,971
in recent years.

978
01:44:57,101 --> 01:45:00,377
ln my opinion, Rebecchi's still
the best tailor in Rome.

979
01:45:03,861 --> 01:45:06,739
- Who are you?
- A hard-working man.

980
01:45:06,861 --> 01:45:11,651
One who, while you play the artist
and have fun with your friends,

981
01:45:11,781 --> 01:45:14,056
keeps this country going.

982
01:45:14,181 --> 01:45:16,775
l keep this country going,

983
01:45:16,901 --> 01:45:19,574
but many people
haven't understood that yet.

984
01:45:22,261 --> 01:45:26,777
lmagine that, Dadina,
Giulio Moneta was my neighbour.

985
01:45:26,901 --> 01:45:32,259
One of the world's 10 most wanted
men and l never noticed.

986
01:45:32,381 --> 01:45:35,134
You've changed,
you're always thinking.

987
01:45:37,581 --> 01:45:39,856
Maybe l should do what Romano did.

988
01:45:40,741 --> 01:45:42,936
l'm not fit for this life
or this city.

989
01:45:43,061 --> 01:45:47,532
Nobody's fit for shit, dammit.
Take it from the queen of misfits.

990
01:45:48,861 --> 01:45:51,329
Everything around me is dying.

991
01:45:52,301 --> 01:45:55,418
People who are younger than me,
things...

992
01:45:56,261 --> 01:45:57,455
All before my eyes and l...

993
01:45:57,581 --> 01:46:01,017
And you're suffering.
And you don't understand.

994
01:46:08,741 --> 01:46:11,175
How's the soup, Little Jep?

995
01:46:13,741 --> 01:46:15,459
The soup's good.

996
01:46:17,661 --> 01:46:21,495
Why did you call me Little Jep? No
one's called me that for centuries.

997
01:46:21,621 --> 01:46:23,896
Because a friend,
every now and again,

998
01:46:24,061 --> 01:46:27,497
needs to make their friend
feel like they did as a child.

999
01:46:29,461 --> 01:46:31,975
How can l make you feel
like a little girl?

1000
01:46:32,101 --> 01:46:34,934
You don't need to, l feel
like a little girl every day!

1001
01:46:35,061 --> 01:46:38,610
l've seen the world from
their viewpoint for 60 years.

1002
01:46:39,901 --> 01:46:42,051
You know Sister Maria,
the missionary,

1003
01:46:42,701 --> 01:46:44,180
the one they call the Saint?

1004
01:46:44,301 --> 01:46:48,135
Yes, she's coming to Rome
to receive some honour.

1005
01:46:48,261 --> 01:46:51,537
Exactly. ln all her life,
she's only given three interviews.

1006
01:46:51,661 --> 01:46:55,176
- Yours will be memorable.
- Yeah sure, think of Giulio Moneta!

1007
01:46:55,301 --> 01:46:59,089
This is different.
She studied in ltaly

1008
01:46:59,221 --> 01:47:02,133
and speaks ltalian.
She read your book and loved it.

1009
01:47:02,741 --> 01:47:04,060
She wants to meet you

1010
01:47:04,181 --> 01:47:06,376
so l organised a dinner party
at your house tomorrow.

1011
01:47:06,501 --> 01:47:09,971
- Did l do well?
- You did very well.

1012
01:49:07,981 --> 01:49:11,656
Tomorrow l'll have the honour
of dining with her.

1013
01:49:11,781 --> 01:49:14,215
- At the Holy Father's?
- No.

1014
01:49:14,381 --> 01:49:15,894
No, at Jep Gambardella's.

1015
01:49:16,661 --> 01:49:22,418
You see, the Pope even invited
the enclosed nuns.

1016
01:49:56,181 --> 01:49:58,695
Sisters, sisters, sisters!

1017
01:49:59,621 --> 01:50:01,452
Sisters, sisters...
Yes, perfect!

1018
01:50:03,861 --> 01:50:06,170
Ah, the Red Cross nurses!
Well-toned!

1019
01:50:06,341 --> 01:50:09,139
Okay, great...
What handsome young men!

1020
01:50:09,661 --> 01:50:10,935
Great!

1021
01:50:11,501 --> 01:50:12,900
Let's go!

1022
01:50:16,581 --> 01:50:18,537
The Saint's assistant called me.

1023
01:50:18,661 --> 01:50:22,415
The Saint would like Count and
Countess Odescalchi to come too,

1024
01:50:22,541 --> 01:50:24,611
as they treated her like a sister
when she lived in ltaly.

1025
01:50:24,741 --> 01:50:28,017
- Do you know them? - Of course,
but they are not in Rome.

1026
01:50:28,141 --> 01:50:31,417
All the nobles are in London,
at Philip's great-niece's wedding.

1027
01:50:31,541 --> 01:50:34,533
Let's call the Colonnas of Reggio.

1028
01:50:34,661 --> 01:50:36,458
The nobles for hire?
They're dead.

1029
01:50:37,341 --> 01:50:39,059
Nonsense, they're immortal.

1030
01:50:39,181 --> 01:50:42,696
The Saint won't even notice,
70 years have gone by!

1031
01:50:43,421 --> 01:50:45,491
This piece of furniture
looks great...

1032
01:50:45,661 --> 01:50:50,257
- Who would've thought!
- lt looks great, like a new bathroom!

1033
01:50:54,701 --> 01:50:56,771
Count Colonna speaking.

1034
01:50:57,381 --> 01:50:59,690
Yes, we are available.

1035
01:51:00,701 --> 01:51:02,259
For tonight.

1036
01:51:02,461 --> 01:51:05,976
Our rate is 250 euros per person
for the evening.

1037
01:51:06,701 --> 01:51:09,818
Plus the cost of the car hire.

1038
01:51:10,901 --> 01:51:15,338
This would be somewhat
humiliating for us...

1039
01:51:16,061 --> 01:51:20,418
We are willing to be hired
as the Colonnas of Reggio.

1040
01:51:21,141 --> 01:51:25,214
But as for pretending to be
the Odescalchis...

1041
01:51:25,581 --> 01:51:26,775
l don't know...

1042
01:51:28,061 --> 01:51:30,734
We were at war for two centuries.

1043
01:51:31,501 --> 01:51:33,298
l feel it's immoral.

1044
01:51:33,741 --> 01:51:37,939
Cut at least twelve pieces
of rabbit!

1045
01:51:38,301 --> 01:51:41,737
Set aside the kidneys, liver,
head...

1046
01:51:41,941 --> 01:51:43,818
Gently brown.

1047
01:51:44,661 --> 01:51:47,255
Don't forget thyme,
laurel leaves, rosemary...

1048
01:51:47,381 --> 01:51:51,579
Then red wine, Ligurian olives...
pine nuts.

1049
01:51:52,461 --> 01:51:55,419
And after an hour,
you have Ligurian-style rabbit!

1050
01:51:56,101 --> 01:51:58,410
Sister Maria, what convent
are you staying at?

1051
01:51:58,541 --> 01:52:02,329
Actually, we're at the Hassler Hotel
at the Spanish Steps.

1052
01:52:03,301 --> 01:52:05,895
To be honest, Sister Maria
finds it uncomfortable.

1053
01:52:06,021 --> 01:52:08,489
Never heard the Hassler
described as uncomfortable!

1054
01:52:09,101 --> 01:52:10,534
lt's very comfortable

1055
01:52:10,661 --> 01:52:13,812
but Sister Maria isn't used
to sleeping in a bed.

1056
01:52:14,381 --> 01:52:17,498
She sleeps on the floor,
in a cardboard bed.

1057
01:52:17,621 --> 01:52:19,612
Do you have any visits planned?

1058
01:52:19,741 --> 01:52:21,572
Sister Maria will climb

1059
01:52:21,701 --> 01:52:23,851
St John's Basilica's Scala Sancta
on her knees.

1060
01:52:24,141 --> 01:52:26,655
- Have you?
- l'd have liked to, but...

1061
01:52:26,781 --> 01:52:29,614
l have a bad knee...

1062
01:52:29,741 --> 01:52:32,209
Orthopedic problems
are unimportant,

1063
01:52:32,421 --> 01:52:37,017
compared to the partial indulgence
granted by the Scala Sancta.

1064
01:52:37,141 --> 01:52:41,657
That's true! Another speciality
of mine is lamb with...

1065
01:52:41,781 --> 01:52:44,739
Does Sister Maria still help
the sick?

1066
01:52:45,021 --> 01:52:47,979
22 hours a day, every day.

1067
01:52:48,141 --> 01:52:51,497
She washes them, feeds them...
You ought to see her.

1068
01:52:51,661 --> 01:52:54,129
Despite her age,
she doesn't walk, she runs.

1069
01:52:54,261 --> 01:53:00,257
Now she's tired, but that's because
she's not with her patients.

1070
01:53:00,421 --> 01:53:01,934
How old is she?

1071
01:53:02,061 --> 01:53:03,972
She'll be 104 in October.

1072
01:53:04,141 --> 01:53:06,291
- That's impressive.
- l thought she was older!

1073
01:53:06,461 --> 01:53:11,216
Longevity too, like all things,
is not accidental.

1074
01:53:11,381 --> 01:53:13,895
About Sister Maria's interview
with Jep...

1075
01:53:14,021 --> 01:53:18,970
Her interview?
There must be a mix-up...

1076
01:53:19,101 --> 01:53:21,899
Sister Maria hasn't given
any interviews since 1971,

1077
01:53:22,021 --> 01:53:24,660
after the reason
for her mission in Chad,

1078
01:53:24,781 --> 01:53:27,420
was misunderstood by some.

1079
01:53:27,901 --> 01:53:30,893
Of course, but considering
her admiration for Jep's work...

1080
01:53:31,061 --> 01:53:33,336
You told me she enjoyed
"The Human Apparatus".

1081
01:53:33,501 --> 01:53:36,618
She found it beautiful and fierce.

1082
01:53:36,741 --> 01:53:38,652
Like the world of men.

1083
01:53:38,781 --> 01:53:41,375
Great! There would be no risk
of any misunderstanding,

1084
01:53:41,541 --> 01:53:43,372
Sister Maria can review the text...

1085
01:53:43,581 --> 01:53:46,573
- No, l'm sorry.
- Don't insist.

1086
01:53:46,741 --> 01:53:50,017
l don't wish to raise
any false hopes,

1087
01:53:50,141 --> 01:53:53,577
there's absolutely
no question of any interview.

1088
01:53:53,701 --> 01:53:56,534
Sorry, but why do
you always answer?

1089
01:53:56,661 --> 01:53:58,697
Why not let Sister Maria talk?

1090
01:54:17,141 --> 01:54:19,450
Madam...

1091
01:54:22,141 --> 01:54:26,134
l took a vow of poverty.

1092
01:54:27,901 --> 01:54:32,213
And you can't talk about poverty...

1093
01:54:33,861 --> 01:54:35,533
you have to live it.

1094
01:54:46,421 --> 01:54:50,255
Such true and real words!
Powerful words!

1095
01:54:54,221 --> 01:54:56,212
Do you need anything, madam?

1096
01:54:56,861 --> 01:54:59,136
- She needs the bathroom.
- lt's on the left.

1097
01:54:59,301 --> 01:55:01,974
The change of diet
isn't good for her.

1098
01:55:02,101 --> 01:55:08,290
Sister Maria, in Mali, only eats
40 grams of plant roots a day.

1099
01:55:08,581 --> 01:55:11,857
Me too sometimes, in the evening,
as a light meal,

1100
01:55:11,981 --> 01:55:15,417
l have some splendid
roots with lemon.

1101
01:55:15,541 --> 01:55:18,658
You clean the roots
by scraping them with a knife

1102
01:55:18,861 --> 01:55:22,171
and you cut them into small
chunks...

1103
01:55:22,381 --> 01:55:25,578
Cardinal, remember when we met
at that wedding?

1104
01:55:25,781 --> 01:55:27,453
You were there too...

1105
01:55:28,941 --> 01:55:33,969
l felt the need to ask you
about matters close to my heart.

1106
01:55:34,221 --> 01:55:36,689
Matters regarding faith...

1107
01:55:37,021 --> 01:55:40,696
regarding the strength
of spirituality...

1108
01:55:41,021 --> 01:55:43,012
But then you got distracted.

1109
01:55:43,181 --> 01:55:44,580
You can ask me now.

1110
01:55:46,461 --> 01:55:50,010
- No, l don't see the point.
- Why?

1111
01:55:50,141 --> 01:55:55,738
l'd be very disappointed to discover
that you have no answers.

1112
01:55:56,221 --> 01:55:58,815
l'm only saying
it's a possibility...

1113
01:55:58,941 --> 01:56:00,818
l think that...

1114
01:56:06,981 --> 01:56:08,096
Never mind...

1115
01:56:13,381 --> 01:56:15,019
l apologize for earlier.

1116
01:56:15,221 --> 01:56:18,736
There is one question
l really want to ask you.

1117
01:56:19,821 --> 01:56:22,381
Are the rumours about you true?

1118
01:56:23,421 --> 01:56:25,298
That you were a truly great...

1119
01:56:27,341 --> 01:56:29,013
exorcist?

1120
01:56:56,861 --> 01:56:58,692
Sister Maria...

1121
01:56:59,221 --> 01:57:00,700
Sister Maria!

1122
01:57:02,661 --> 01:57:04,219
- Sister Maria!
- Saint...

1123
01:57:04,341 --> 01:57:06,172
- Have you seen her?
- No, she's not there.

1124
01:57:08,541 --> 01:57:10,259
- Sister Maria!
- Saint...

1125
01:57:10,381 --> 01:57:11,609
Sister Maria!

1126
01:57:11,741 --> 01:57:12,776
Saint!

1127
01:57:12,901 --> 01:57:15,574
She's called Sister Maria.

1128
01:57:15,701 --> 01:57:17,339
Sister Maria...

1129
01:57:17,461 --> 01:57:20,259
Where has that bitch got to?

1130
01:57:44,301 --> 01:57:46,132
Sister Maria!

1131
01:57:48,941 --> 01:57:50,897
Sister Maria!

1132
01:57:53,341 --> 01:57:54,694
My goodness!

1133
01:57:56,061 --> 01:57:57,813
My goodness!

1134
01:58:28,861 --> 01:58:31,694
Come, Elisabetta, let's go to bed.

1135
01:58:31,861 --> 01:58:34,739
You go ahead, l'm going upstairs
for a moment.

1136
01:58:35,981 --> 01:58:38,051
Don't be late.

1137
01:59:49,621 --> 01:59:52,419
ln this room, in 1930,

1138
01:59:52,541 --> 01:59:55,931
Princess Antonietta gave birth
to her only daughter,

1139
01:59:56,061 --> 01:59:58,256
Elisabetta Colonna of Reggio.

1140
01:59:58,621 --> 02:00:01,658
The princess died
after giving birth.

1141
02:00:01,781 --> 02:00:04,659
Young Elisabetta,
in these opulent rooms,

1142
02:00:04,781 --> 02:00:07,534
had a happy and carefree
childhood.

1143
02:00:07,661 --> 02:00:12,371
But shortly after, the financial
hardship endured by Prince Erminio,

1144
02:00:12,981 --> 02:00:15,734
forced him to sell the property.

1145
02:00:51,181 --> 02:00:53,217
They're migrating west...

1146
02:00:53,381 --> 02:00:57,294
but now they are resting.

1147
02:01:10,581 --> 02:01:12,219
Did you know

1148
02:01:13,141 --> 02:01:17,419
that l know the Christian names...

1149
02:01:18,021 --> 02:01:21,980
of all of these birds?

1150
02:01:29,381 --> 02:01:30,496
Why...

1151
02:01:32,261 --> 02:01:35,697
did you never write another book?

1152
02:01:41,861 --> 02:01:43,613
l was looking for the great beauty,

1153
02:01:45,701 --> 02:01:47,339
but...

1154
02:01:50,461 --> 02:01:51,655
l didn't find it.

1155
02:01:53,501 --> 02:01:55,219
Do you know...

1156
02:01:56,021 --> 02:01:57,534
why...

1157
02:01:58,221 --> 02:02:01,133
l only eat roots?

1158
02:02:06,461 --> 02:02:08,053
No, why?

1159
02:02:14,981 --> 02:02:19,372
Because roots are important.

1160
02:04:48,541 --> 02:04:52,295
Now there's something
l want to show you.

1161
02:05:51,141 --> 02:05:54,611
This is how it always ends.
With death.

1162
02:05:55,821 --> 02:05:59,052
But first there was life.

1163
02:05:59,541 --> 02:06:03,420
Hidden beneath the blah, blah, blah.

1164
02:06:05,781 --> 02:06:10,536
lt is all settled beneath
the chitter chatter and the noise.

1165
02:06:11,341 --> 02:06:14,697
Silence and sentiment.

1166
02:06:15,181 --> 02:06:18,173
Emotion and fear.

1167
02:06:19,381 --> 02:06:24,694
The haggard, inconstant
flashes of beauty.

1168
02:06:25,421 --> 02:06:30,495
And then the wretched squalor
and miserable humanity.

1169
02:06:31,621 --> 02:06:36,012
All buried under the cover of the
embarrassment of being in the world.

1170
02:06:41,221 --> 02:06:44,736
Beyond there is what lies beyond.

1171
02:06:45,741 --> 02:06:49,131
l don't deal
with what lies beyond.

1172
02:06:50,221 --> 02:06:55,011
Therefore...
let this novel begin.

1173
02:06:55,861 --> 02:06:59,695
After all... it's just a trick.

1174
02:07:00,661 --> 02:07:04,336
Yes, it's just a trick.
